/tmux/persistence.ts` — P54 persistence (criterion 3)\n- `src/hooks/pane-monitor.ts` — P53 hook (criterion 1)\n\n## CP8 PLAN-CHECK (12-dimension, target: PASS 0/0/0)\n\nMatch `54-PLAN-CHECK.md` structure. Verify:\n- 4 EARS covered (REQ-55-01..04 → T1 + T2 + T3)\n- 4 tasks valid (Files + Action + Verify + Done)\n- Dependency graph acyclic\n- 12 D-55 decisions honored\n- L1 evidence quality (BATS commands present)\n- File scope: 4 BATS + 1 helpers.bash + 1 UAT report\n- Guardrails: R-P50-03, D-04, P20 invariant, 27-tool-key unchanged\n- Test coverage: 4 BATS scenarios\n- GATE logic: 3/4 PASS = advance; 2/4 = P56 retry\n- SC-isolation: no SC-* references\n- Atomic commit: T4 uses both `git add <new paths>` and explicit staging (per P53 BLOCKER-2 fix)\n- Verdict: **must be PASS**\n\nCommit: `55-PLAN-CHECK.md` with message `P55 Checkpoint 8: 55-PLAN-CHECK.md — verdict PASS, 0 findings`\n\n## CP9 EXECUTE (4 BATS + UAT report + atomic commit)\n\n### T1: Create 4 BATS scenarios\n\nEach BATS uses `load \"helpers\"`, `tmux_bats_require_dist`, and cleans up tmux session in teardown.\n\n**57-live-pane-monitoring.bats**:\n- Spawn tmux session with `sleep 60`\n- Invoke `pane-monitor.ts:createPaneMonitorHook` via `tmux_node_eval`\n- Dispatch synthetic `pane-captured` event through observer main path: `await observer({ event: { type: \"pane-captured\", sessionId: \"test-session\", paneId: \"%0\", contentLength: 1024, timestamp: Date.now() } })`\n- Wait 200ms\n- Assert journal file at `.hivemind/journal/test-session/<ISO>-pane.json` exists\n- jq: 7 fields, schemaVersion=1, eventType=pane-captured, retryCount=0\n- Teardown: `tmux kill-session`\n\n**58-orchestrator-intervention.bats**:\n- Spawn tmux session running `cat` (reads stdin)\n- `tmux send-keys -t <session> \"hello-from-test\"` literal\n- `tmux send-keys -t <session> Enter`\n- Wait 100ms\n- `tmux capture-pane -t <session> -p` should contain \"hello-from-test\"\n- Teardown: `tmux kill-session`\n\n**59-session-persistence-restart.bats**:\n- Spawn tmux session with `sleep 600`\n- Write persistence file: state=paused via `tmux_node_eval` (invoke `persistence.persist({...state: 'paused'})`)\n- Verify session alive: `tmux has-session -t <session>` returns 0\n- \"Kill harness\": just exit the BATS subshell with `exit 0` (no actual kill needed since BATS restarts on next `@test` invocation)\n- On BATS restart (separate test invocation), `tmux_node_eval` to invoke `persistence.restoreAll()` and verify the persisted session is in the returned list\n- Teardown: `tmux kill-session`\n\n**60-visual-dependency-graph.bats**:\n- `tmux_node_eval` to invoke `grid-planner.ts:computeSplitSequence` with a mock delegation tree\n- Assert the returned split sequence is a valid DFS layout (e.g., root pane at center, children at perimeter)\n- Verify all panes are non-overlapping\n\n### T2: Run BATS L1 verification\n\n```bash\nnpx tsc\nbats --jobs 1 tests/scripts/tmux/57-live-pane-monitoring.bats\nbats --jobs 1 tests/scripts/tmux/58-orchestrator-intervention.bats\nbats --jobs 1 tests/scripts/tmux/59-session-persistence-restart.bats\nbats --jobs 1 tests/scripts/tmux/60-visual-dependency-graph.bats\n```\n\n### T3: Author `.planning/phases/55-e2e-uat-against-seed-success-criteria/55-E2E-UAT-2026-06-02.md`\n\nMatch ROADMAP L2018 directive. Sections per D-55-09:\n- 1. Live pane monitoring (criterion 1): L1 (BATS output) + L2 (text-described screenshot of tmux grid) + verdict\n- 2. Orchestrator intervention (criterion 2): L1 + L2 + verdict\n- 3. Session persistence (criterion 3): L1 + L2 + verdict\n- 4. Visual dependency graph (criterion 4): L1 + L2 + verdict\n- 5. GATE: count PASS, apply D-55-04 logic (3/4 advance, 2/4 P56 retry)\n- 6. Final verdict\n\n### T4: Atomic commit\n\n```bash\ngit add tests/scripts/tmux/57-live-pane-monitoring.bats tests/scripts/tmux/58-orchestrator-intervention.bats tests/scripts/tmux/59-session-persistence-restart.bats tests/scripts/tmux/60-visual-dependency-graph.bats tests/scripts/tmux/helpers.bash\ngit add .planning/phases/55-e2e-uat-against-seed-success-criteria/55-E2E-UAT-2026-06-02.md\n```\n\nCommit with message:\n```\nP55 Checkpoint 9: EXECUTE — 4 BATS + UAT report + atomic commit\n\n- 57-live-pane-monitoring.bats: criterion 1 (P53 integration)\n- 58-orchestrator-intervention.bats: criterion 2 (send-keys + capture-pane)\n- 59-session-persistence-restart.bats: criterion 3 (P54 integration)\n- 60-visual-dependency-graph.bats: criterion 4 (grid-planner DFS)\n- 55-E2E-UAT-2026-06-02.md: L1+L2 evidence + GATE verdict\n- GATE: <PASS|FAIL> based on per-criterion count\n```\n\n## CP10 VERIFY (independent re-validation)\n\nAfter EXECUTE, run L1 commands again to verify:\n- `npx tsc --noEmit` exit 0\n- `bats --jobs 1 tests/scripts/tmux/5[7-9]-*.bats tests/scripts/tmux/60-*.bats` all pass\n- `git show --name-only HEAD | grep -c hivemind` = 0\n- 27 tool keys unchanged\n- 4 EARS covered\n\nAmend `55-E2E-UAT-2026-06-02.md` with a `## Re-Verification Verdict` section. Commit:\n```\nP55 Checkpoint 10: VERIFY — 55-E2E-UAT-2026-06-02.md re-verified\n```\n\n## EXECUTION GUARDRAILS\n\n1. **USE TOOLS** — every step uses Read/Write/Edit/Bash.\n2. **100% PASS at plan-check** — fix any blockers inline before reporting.\n3. **DO NOT** modify source files; only planning + tests + report.\n4. **DO NOT** touch `.hivemind/session-tracker/*` (R-P50-03).\n5. **SC-isolation**: no SC-* references.\n6. **Empty result failure pattern** — DO NOT return with no tool calls.\n\nWhen complete, return:\n```\n###TASK_COMPLETED###\nP55 PLAN-CHECK: PASS 0/0/0 (commit <hash1>)\nP55 EXECUTE: 4 BATS + UAT report + atomic commit (commit <hash2>)\nP55 VERIFY: re-verification (commit <hash3>)\nGATE verdict: <3/4 PASS advance | 2/4 FAIL P56 retry>\n```",
